      <akn:section eId="sec_28_4906">
        <akn:num>28-4906</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Legal recognition of electronic records, electronic signatures, and electronic contracts.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-4906_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A record or signature may not be denied legal effect or enforceability solely because it is in electronic form.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-4906_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A contract may not be denied legal effect or enforceability solely because an electronic record was used in its formation.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-4906_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>If a law requires a record to be in writing, an electronic record satisfies the law.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-4906_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>If a law requires a signature, an electronic signature satisfies the law.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
